'''Santiago Rodríguez Masagó''' (c. 1809 – 27 May 1879), also known as '''Santiago Rodríguez''', nicknamed "Chago" was a [[Dominican people (Dominican Republic)|Dominican]] military leader. Little is known of his birth but sources suggest that he was either born in [[Cap-Haïtien]]<ref name="Salamador"/><ref>[http://www.encaribe.org/es/article/santiago-rodriguez/1231 En Caribe - Santiago Rodríguez: Historia, República Dominicana] {{es}}</ref> or the area of [[Fort-Liberté]] (in a part where it is present day [[Dajabón]]). He is known for having opposed the annexation of the [[Dominican Republic]] to [[Spain]] and then having fought the [[History of Spain (1810–73)|Spanish Crown]]; and for being one of the rebels of the famous ''El Grito de Capotillo'' that began the [[Dominican Restoration War]] with General [[Gregorio Luperón]].

==Early years==
Although little is known about his origin, many historians agree that the son of the landowner Vicente Rodríguez and Josefina Masagó (of [[Haiti]]an descent),<ref name="Salamador"/><ref name="Dominguez Cruz"/> two wealthy merchants from the city of [[Santiago Province (Dominican Republic)|Santiago]] in the Dominican Republic.<ref name="Salamador">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7stsAAAAMAAJ&q=Santiago+Rodr%C3%ADguez+Masag%C3%B3+haiti&dq=Santiago+Rodr%C3%ADguez+Masag%C3%B3+haiti&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjX55jQl5nNAhVJdR4KHe-FBggQ6AEIHDAA |title=José Francisco Peña Gómez: sus orígenes, su biografía, su personalidad, su pensamiento |editor=Salamador, Victor |page=36 |year=1990 |accessdate=8 June 2016}} {{es}}</ref><ref name="Dominguez Cruz">{{cite web|url=http://diariodigital.com.do/santiago-rodriguez-el-patriota-ignorado/ |title=Santiago Rodríguez: El patriota ignorado |editor=Dominguez Cruz, Franklin |publisher=Diario Digital |date=29 January 2006 |accessdate=21 July 2014}} {{es}}</ref>

==Military career==
After the Restoration of the country, Rodríguez held various military occupations.

==Death and legacy==
He died on May 24, 1879 in Agua Clara, Sabaneta Spanish.

